I can only provide a review for brunch as I have not tried their dinner, but I have to say this is absolutely a solid brunch option in Wicker Park! So much so, that I have driven multiple times from Lincoln Square just to dine here. Given that this review is a summary of all of my visits, I have to warn that some menu items have been rotated out.  Pockets Restaurant always has fantastic pastry options, so if you're not carb-averse, definitely order this for the table. My absolute favorites are the biscuit and cinnamon roll (if it hasn't run out for the morning).  In terms of other menu items, they have some Italian-inspired items like pizza, Mexican-inspired items like huevos rancheros and then some more classic brunch items. Their huevos rancheros (and in the past, their pozole) were definitely solid! You can't go wrong in ordering that. The pizza is quite delicious too. I have also had the pleasure of eating their breakfast sandwich and their fried chicken with a biscuit. While both decent, I can't say that they particularly stand out, but if you're not feeling the other items, they're still a good choice.  It honestly tasted like tomato juice with spice. The mix didn't have the body I tend to love.
